		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/today-in-small-business-buying-american/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Buying American" data-description="Understanding who uses Pinterest and how. Some employees feel guilty about taking breaks. On the front lines of climate change in Florida.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Social Media</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ This infographic displays the &#8220;<a href="//www.coolinfographics.com/blog/2014/5/7/the-dead-zones-when-not-to-post-on-social-media.html?">dead zones</a>&#8221; when it&#8217;s probably not a good idea to post anything on various social media sites.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s a break down ofÂ <a href="blog.rjmetrics.com/2014/05/07/pinners-be-pinnin-how-to-justify-pinterests-3-8b-valuation/">who uses Pinterest</a> and how.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Economic performance in the first quarter is <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-05-06/first-quarter-u-s-economic-slump-looking-uglier-by-the-day.html">looking uglier</a> by the day.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ And <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/05/07/vital-signs-productivity-growth-is-still-struggling/?omics+Blog%29">output per hour worked</a> in the non-farm business sector fell at a 1.7 percent annual rate in the first quarter.</p>
